snippet.textDisplay: Just because on paper it looks like the s20 is better than the iPhone doesn’t mean it actually is. For example Samsung calmed that the galaxy j6 has a 13mp camera on the rear but yet the note 10+ only has a 12mp. However the photos on the note 10 are far better than the j6. I’ve got an iPhone 11 Pro and an s20 ultra. The iPhone scored higher in geekbench and both are as smooth as each other. I download cod mobile and used a frame rate tracker. The s20 got 32fps and the iPhone got 87fps. I also compared cameras, the iPhone 11 Pro photos were brighter had more detail and far better colour accuracy and dynamic range. Lowlight performances in my opinion was identical. The 8k video kept on crashing  my s20. And don’t forget Apple have got deep fusion which can capture loads more detail. Don’t just assume 1 phone is better because of the specs on paper.
snippet.textOriginal: Just because on paper it looks like the s20 is better than the iPhone doesn’t mean it actually is. For example Samsung calmed that the galaxy j6 has a 13mp camera on the rear but yet the note 10+ only has a 12mp. However the photos on the note 10 are far better than the j6. I’ve got an iPhone 11 Pro and an s20 ultra. The iPhone scored higher in geekbench and both are as smooth as each other. I download cod mobile and used a frame rate tracker. The s20 got 32fps and the iPhone got 87fps. I also compared cameras, the iPhone 11 Pro photos were brighter had more detail and far better colour accuracy and dynamic range. Lowlight performances in my opinion was identical. The 8k video kept on crashing  my s20. And don’t forget Apple have got deep fusion which can capture loads more detail. Don’t just assume 1 phone is better because of the specs on paper.
